{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\n\nThree follow-ups spun out of dc3f (puzzling-obsidian-bunny) after its core gap — 3 undeployed\nCloudWatch alarms — was fixed by a terraform apply: (1) confirm the alert SNS subscription\nactually delivers, (2) add terraform drift-detection CI so committed-but-unapplied HCL cannot\nsit unnoticed (the root cause of dc3f), and (3) bring a live-but-unmanaged alarm under IaC.\n\nThese are bundled deliberately: all three harden the SAME alerting/IaC chain for the rebar-gerrit\nhost and are small. Each AC below names a single unambiguous disposition (no open design choice\nleft to the executor).\n\n## Scope\n\n- rebar-gerrit-alerts SNS email subscription (the alert sink).\n- No terraform CI exists (apply is manual per infra/runbooks/provision-restore.md), so committed\n  HCL can silently sit unapplied — the dc3f root cause.\n- One live alarm (rebar-gerrit-data-disk-high) exists in AWS but is absent from HCL/state and has\n  an EMPTY alarm_actions list (never notifies).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] [operator-attested] AC1 — SNS subscription delivers. The rebar-gerrit-alerts email\n  subscription to joeoakhart@navapbc.com is CONFIRMED (not PendingConfirmation) so alarms\n  actually deliver. Evidence: a ticket comment recording the get-subscription-attributes result\n  (PendingConfirmation=false) with the SubscriptionArn and date. NOTE: verified 2026-07-11 —\n  PendingConfirmation=false; this AC is already met and needs NO destructive replacement sink.\n- [ ] AC2a — OIDC role (least-privilege, plan-only). The GitHub OIDC provider\n  (token.actions.githubusercontent.com) ALREADY EXISTS in account 896586841071 (verified); this\n  ticket adds a NEW IAM role `rebar-terraform-plan` in infra/terraform/iam.tf whose trust policy\n  is scoped to `repo:navapbc/rebar:*` (sub condition) with aud=sts.amazonaws.com, and whose\n  permissions are AWS-managed ReadOnlyAccess + one inline statement granting kms:Decrypt\n  constrained by kms:ViaService=ssm (for the alert-endpoint SecureString data source). No apply\n  or write permissions — plan-only, least privilege.\n- [ ] AC2b — drift-detection CI. `.github/workflows/terraform-drift.yml` runs\n  `terraform plan -input=false -lock=false -detailed-exitcode` in infra/terraform, authenticating\n  via GitHub OIDC to `rebar-terraform-plan`. `-detailed-exitcode` makes a non-empty plan (exit 2)\n  FAIL the check. Triggers: pull_request touching infra/terraform/**, push to main touching\n  infra/terraform/** (catches already-committed-but-unapplied drift, not just PR diffs), a daily\n  schedule, and workflow_dispatch.\n- [ ] AC3 — codify + import the orphan alarm (keep coverage; non-destructive). Add\n  `aws_cloudwatch_metric_alarm.gerrit_data_disk_high` (name rebar-gerrit-data-disk-high;\n  namespace rebar/host, metric disk_used_percent published by observability.sh, dims\n  InstanceId=data.aws_instance.gerrit.id + mount=/var/gerrit, threshold 85, GTE) to\n  infra/terraform/monitoring.tf WITH alarm_actions/ok_actions = the SNS topic (closing the\n  silent-alarm gap), then `terraform import` it into state so HCL/state/reality agree. The alarm\n  is KEPT (data-volume disk pressure is real coverage), not deleted.\n\n## Verification\n\n- AC1: `aws sns get-subscription-attributes` shows PendingConfirmation=false (recorded as a\n  comment).\n- AC2/AC3: `terraform validate` passes and `terraform plan` (ReadOnlyAccess creds) shows the new\n  role/policies/alarm apply cleanly with no errors — run pre-merge in the worktree.\n- Post-merge operator step (needs live creds): `terraform import\n  aws_cloudwatch_metric_alarm.gerrit_data_disk_high rebar-gerrit-data-disk-high` then\n  `terraform apply` to wire the alarm actions and create the role; the terraform-drift CI then\n  reports green (no drift) on the next run.\n\n## Notes / decisions (resolve prior plan-review BLOCKs)\n\n- Shared S3 state backend (rebar-tfstate-896586841071) means terraform writes (import/apply) MUST\n  follow the HCL merge — importing to shared state before merge would make an un-branched plan\n  read the alarm as \"to destroy\". So this ticket lands the reviewed HCL/CI via Gerrit; the\n  import/apply is the documented post-merge operator step above.\n- AC1's original \"OR replace with a confirmation-free sink\" option is dropped: the subscription is\n  already confirmed, so no destructive substitution (which risked dark alerting) is needed."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783784086929623001,"uuid":"cbd2cb3a-b2f7-4dca-86da-0944a29c0866"}